<AbstractNarration>This project will attempt to develop an interferometric synthetic aperature sonar system for use on oceanographic research ships.  Two technical developments will be necessary: formation of a synthetic aperature sonar image, and differencing the phase of the reference and repeat images to form a sonar interferogram.  The simrad EM120 multibeam system on the R/V Roger Revelle will be used.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
